    <main class="page">
      <div class="lesson-bubble">
        <h1>üé£ Spotting Scams & Phishing</h1>

        <p><strong>What is phishing?</strong><br>
        Phishing is when someone pretends to be a trusted person or company to trick you into giving away personal information like passwords, credit card numbers, or private photos. It's called "phishing" because scammers are "fishing" for your data!</p>

        <h2>Common Signs of a Scam</h2>
        <div class="warning-box">
          <h3>‚ö†Ô∏è Red Flags to Watch For:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Urgent language:</strong> "Act NOW!" or "Your account will be deleted in 24 hours!"</li>
            <li><strong>Requests for passwords:</strong> Real companies NEVER ask for your password via email</li>
            <li><strong>Weird links:</strong> URLs that look misspelled or suspicious (micr0soft.com instead of microsoft.com)</li>
            <li><strong>Too good to be true:</strong> "You won $1,000,000!" or "Free iPhone!"</li>
            <li><strong>Unexpected attachments:</strong> Files you didn't ask for from people you don't know</li>
            <li><strong>Poor grammar:</strong> Lots of spelling mistakes or odd wording</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>Real-World Example</h2>
        <div class="scam-example">
          "URGENT! Your Netflix account will be suspended in 24 hours unless you verify your payment information. Click here immediately: http://netfl1x-verify.com"
        </div>
        <p><strong>Why this is a scam:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Uses urgency to make you panic</li>
          <li>The link is NOT the real Netflix URL (notice the "1" instead of "i")</li>
          <li>Real companies contact you through their official app or website</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Stay Safe</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Don't click suspicious links</strong> ‚Äì Go directly to the website instead</li>
          <li><strong>Verify the sender</strong> ‚Äì Check the email address carefully</li>
          <li><strong>Don't download random files</strong> ‚Äì They could contain viruses</li>
          <li><strong>Ask an adult</strong> ‚Äì If something feels wrong, it probably is</li>
          <li><strong>Report scams</strong> ‚Äì Mark emails as spam to help others</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Remember This</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 600; color: #2f6fff; text-align: center; padding: 20px; background: #f0f7ff; border-radius: 12px; margin: 20px 0;">
          Real companies will NEVER ask for your password via email, text, or social media!
        </p>

        <div class="challenge-box">
          <h3>üêµ Monkey Challenge</h3>
          <p>Read this message in your head:</p>
          <div class="scam-example" style="margin: 16px 0;">
            "Congratulations! You've been selected as a winner! Click this link now to claim your prize before it expires!"
          </div>
          <p><strong>Now ask yourself: Who benefits if I panic and click quickly?</strong></p>
          <p style="font-style: italic;">If the answer isn't "you," it's probably a scam. Scammers want you to act before you think!</p>
          
          <h4 style="margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #d97706;">Quick Quiz:</h4>
          <p style="font-style: normal; font-weight: 600; color: #333;">Which message is most likely a scam?</p>
          
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">
            A) A text from your mom asking what you want for dinner
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, true)">
            B) An email saying "Your bank account has been compromised! Click here to verify your identity NOW!"
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">
            C) A notification from your school app about tomorrow's schedule
          </div>
          <div class="quiz-option" onclick="checkAnswer(this, false)">
            D) A message from a friend asking about homework
          </div>

          <div id="quiz-feedback" class="quiz-feedback"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="complete-checkbox">
          <input type="checkbox" id="lesson-complete" onchange="markComplete()">
          <label for="lesson-complete">‚úÖ I've completed this lesson!</label>
        </div>

        <a href="lesson3.html" class="btn">Next Lesson: Digital Footprints ‚Üí</a>
      </div>
    </main>
  </div>

  <script>
    let quizAnswered = false;

    function checkAnswer(element, isCorrect) {
      if (quizAnswered) return;
      
      quizAnswered = true;
      const feedback = document.getElementById('quiz-feedback');
      
      if (isCorrect) {
        element.classList.add('correct');
        feedback.className = 'quiz-feedback correct show';
        feedback.innerHTML = '‚úÖ <strong>Correct!</strong> This message uses urgency ("NOW!"), claims your account is compromised, and asks you to click a link ‚Äì all major red flags for phishing scams!';
      } else {
        element.classList.add('incorrect');
        feedback.className = 'quiz-feedback incorrect show';
        feedback.innerHTML = '‚ùå <strong>Not quite.</strong> Look for messages that create panic, ask for personal info, or demand immediate action. Try again!';
        setTimeout(() => {
          quizAnswered = false;
          element.classList.remove('incorrect');
          feedback.classList.remove('show');
        }, 2500);
      }
    }

    function markComplete() {
      const isChecked = document.getElementById('lesson-complete').checked;
      localStorage.setItem('lesson_scams', isChecked.toString());
      updateProgress();
    }

    function updateProgress() {
      const lessons = ['passwords', 'scams', 'footprints'];
      let completed = 0;

      lessons.forEach(lesson => {
        if (localStorage.getItem(`lesson_${lesson}`) === 'true') {
          completed++;
        }
      });

      const percent = Math.round((completed / lessons.length) * 100);
      
      document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = 
        `Your Progress: ${percent}%`;
      
      const fill = document.getElementById('progress-bar-fill');
      fill.style.width = percent + '%';

      const monkey = document.getElementById('progress-monkey');
      const barWidth = document.getElementById('progress-bar-bg').offsetWidth;
      const monkeyX = (percent / 100) * (barWidth - 50);
      monkey.style.left = monkeyX + 'px';
    }

    // Initialize
    if (localStorage.getItem('lesson_scams') === 'true') {
      document.getElementById('lesson-complete').checked = true;
    }
    updateProgress();
  </script>
